status_message:
At our conference next week, we'll be making a clear commitment to restore civil liberties eroded by the SNP government.

Among the commitments to restore civil liberties that will be included in our manifesto are:

- Scrap SNP plans for a Super ID database;
- Steps to safeguard people from the misuse of their data, CCTV images or biometric information;
- Retain corroboration in criminal cases;
- Extend Freedom of Information legislation to private sector bodies providing public services;
- Establish a formal protocol for helping refugees in Scottish communities, to build on good practice, make sure the right support is available.

These proposals form part of the Scottish Liberal Democrat pre-manifesto that will be debated at conference.
